"{\n    \"language style\": \"The author employs a clear, authoritative, and accessible writing style. The language is formal yet digestible, avoiding overly technical jargon while maintaining scientific credibility. Extensive use of expert quotes adds authority and credibility to the articles. Sentences are typically medium length, balancing information density with readability.\",\n    \n    \"narrative techniques\": \"The articles follow a consistent structural pattern: opening with a broad context, presenting key benefits, supporting with expert testimonials, and concluding with practical advice. The author uses a third-person perspective and maintains an objective tone throughout. Information is presented in logical segments with clear subheadings. Expert quotes are strategically placed to validate main points and break up dense information.\",\n    \n    \"innovation\": \"While the articles follow traditional health journalism formats, they innovate through comprehensive synthesis of complex scientific information into accessible content. The author creates engagement by connecting scientific benefits to everyday life applications. The writing demonstrates skilled integration of multiple expert sources and research findings into cohesive narratives that maintain reader interest despite technical subject matter.\"\n}"